# MDS Dashboard Background with Elevated Cards/Panels

## Rule

When a dashboard page uses elevated white cards or panels (cards with borders, shadows, or visual separation from the background), the dashboard's main background must use:

```css
background: var(--mds-color-background-subtle);
```

This creates proper visual hierarchy and contrast between the white content cards and the surrounding page background.

## DO NOT Apply This Rule When

- Page only has flat tables without card containers
- Content flows directly on the page without card/panel wrappers
- No visual elevation or separation between content sections
- User management or team management pages with plain tables

## Apply This Rule When

- Dashboard has stat cards with white backgrounds and borders/elevation
- Dashboard has white panel sections with visual separation (borders, shadows)
- Dashboard uses Card components from @ui with elevation
- Multiple distinct white content containers on a colored background

## Examples

### ✅ GOOD - Dashboard with White Cards

```css
/* Main dashboard container */
.dashboard {
  min-height: 100vh;
  background: var(--mds-color-background-subtle); /* Subtle background for white cards */
}

/* White cards on subtle background */
.stat-card,
.table-section,
.action-panel {
  background: var(--mds-color-white);
  border: 1px solid var(--mds-color-border-default);
  border-radius: 4px;
  padding: 1.5rem;
}
```

### ✅ GOOD - Analytics Dashboard with Card Components

```css
.analytics-dashboard {
  min-height: 100vh;
  background: var(--mds-color-background-subtle); /* Subtle background */
}

/* Using Card component from @ui (white by default) */
.analytics-main {
  flex: 1;
  padding: 32px 24px;
  background: var(--mds-color-neutral-30);
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Background on Pages Without Elevated Cards

```css
/* User/Team management with flat tables - no background needed */
.user-management {
  background: var(--mds-color-background-subtle); /* Wrong - no elevated cards */
}

/* Dashboard with no visual card separation */
.plain-dashboard {
  background: var(--mds-color-background-subtle); /* Wrong - content is flat */
}
```

### ❌ BAD - Insufficient Contrast with White Cards

```css
/* When you DO have elevated cards, white background is bad */
.dashboard {
  background: var(--mds-color-background-default); /* White - bad contrast */
}
```

## Why This Matters

- **Visual Hierarchy**: Gray background separates white content cards from the page
- **Contrast**: Ensures cards stand out clearly
- **Professional**: Provides depth and dimension to the layout
- **Consistency**: Standard pattern across all dashboard pages
